This paper deals with the problem of interference channels with one cognitive transmitter, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the impact of cognitive ability on the capacity region of the channel, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper proposes a new achievable rate region, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.MM) and communication engineering (cs.CE). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, and cs.CE, in that order.
